EXTREME PROGRAMMING 

* Extreme Programming (XP) is one of the popular Agile methodologies and it is mostly used along with Scrum framework to create a blend of both engineering and management practices in Agile projects. 
* The term XP is conceptualized from the execution of traditional software engineering practices at extreme levels.
* Widely known for its technical practices which can help developers to build high quality software, more productively. 
* There are 12 practices which fall under four key areas:
      # Fine Scale Feedback
      # Continuous Process
      # Shared Understanding
      #  Programmer Welfare

> Fine Scale Programming 
* Planning Game: The key planning process of Extreme Programming is called planning game to ensure workis planned incrementally. It is divided into two parts â€“
        # Release Planning
        # Iteration Planning
